Brand story:
IBM Innovator Begins Second Century
If someone were to look for a word that would most accurately express IBM’s strategy, the closest one would probably be “longevity.”
For the general public, IBM is a symbol of the technological revolution, it is a company perceived as very contemporary, and yet it has been a hundred years since its founding.
The foundation for this long-term development was laid by the company’s first chief executive, visionary Thomas J. Watson Sr.
He has already coined the motto that a number of world problems can be easily solved if people are willing to think.
His slogan "Think!" became the imprint around which the life of the future giant will unfold (and also the name of an internal magazine that began to be published at IBM in 1935).
