It is this material, slightly cut, that forms the basis of the 68-minute film Steve Jobs: A Lost Interview, which targets selected cinemas this Wednesday and Thursday.
For someone who is famous for his reluctance to provide longer interviews, here Jobs seems surprisingly excited to be able to talk about his technological philosophy and business strategies.
He also appears to be a very thoughtful person.
Four times during the interview, there will be a longer pause between the question and the answer - 10 to 15 seconds of thinking, when you see how Jobs thinks the answer perfectly, to be as accurate and accurate as possible.
