The interview was filmed before the era of Pixar, iPod, or iPhone, and it’s filled with frighteningly prophetic thoughts as Jobs assesses what other companies are doing right and wrong, offering his own vision of the future in the field of computer technology.
One thing is to read Jobs' posthumous reviews of his career, but on Jobs, whom we see here as a yearning dreamer in the bloom of his genius, there is something raw and inspiring.
He has his own vision of what things might and should look like.
