A quick summary of seven scenes from The Lost Interview that are definitely worth noting:
How he learned to run a business:
"Over the years of business, I've always asked, 'Why are you doing this?' and the answer has always been the same: 'Well, that's how it's done.'"
No one knows why he does what he does, never thinks deeply about things related to business.
That's what I found out.
Jobs continues by describing his effort to simplify accounting at Apple.
