“We were young and we found that we can build something ourselves that is capable of running billions of dollars of infrastructure around the world.”
The two of us made a little thing that could control a much bigger dragon – it was an incredible experience and I think Apple would never have been created without it.
Jobs goes on to describe a joke that Wozniak and I almost finished. Through the Blue Box in the middle of the night, they called the Vatican and asked if they could talk to the Pope, pretending to be Henry Kissinger as best they could.
