The technological genius that led society to its unshakable position is now replaced by people who have no idea of good or bad products - skill and technical knowledge are necessary.
This is exactly what happened at Xerox.
Xerox could literally own the entire computer industry.
It could have been ten times bigger than it is, it could have been Microsoft of the 1990s...
Instead of winning, however, they lost.
How to take innovation as a form of art:
"There's still a long way to go between a great idea and an excellent result... and as the great idea develops, it changes and grows."
During that time, you will learn a lot about him.
You have to make a whole range of compromises - you just don't force electrons, glass, robots or factories to do certain things.
