How to Recognize a Lie
A quick look at recent newspaper headlines suggests how serious and ubiquitous lies and lies are in everyday life.
Republican presidential candidate Herman Cain has his hands full with the accusation that he sexually harassed several women - both sides claim the other is lying.
Administrators at Penn State University were accused of false testimony when they tried to hide records that a retired football coach sexually assaulted a boy.
