Replacing analog signals with digital signals is one of the biggest changes the world has experienced in recent years. It is related to better use of radio spectrum, better signal quality and more channels.
It believes that postponing the change would delay the benefits of digitalisation, which requires decisions on matters of public interest, since digitalisation has not only a technical dimension, but "also touches on economic, social, political and national security issues".
