Colom approves Portilla's release to the United States
President <0xC3><0x81>lvaro Colom announced on Tuesday that he had taken steps to extradite former President Alfonso Portillo, who is expected to be held accountable in the United States for the $70 million conspiracy to launder.
This is the end of a process aimed at getting Guatemala to respond to a request from a northern country requesting the extradition of Portillo to be tried.
At a press conference, Colom confirmed that his decision was consistent with the independence of the judiciary and the executive branch, and that he remembered that the criminal court had already ordered extradition.
He assured that during his term of office he "did not interfere" in court decisions and allowed all extraditions that came to his table.
In addition to Portilla, Sergio Ruano Marroquín will be released for murder and serious harm to health and Edgar Estrada Morales and Víctor Estrada Paredes, both for drug trafficking.
Colombo's move means a step of execution after all judicial and constitutional instances have been exhausted to lead the process against the former president, who ruled from 2000 to 2004.
In accordance with the decisions of the Fifth Criminal Tribunal and the Constitutional Court (CC), Portillo will be extradited after his legal situation in Guatemala is resolved and human rights are guaranteed.
Portillo was found innocent of the robbery of $120 million to the Department of Defense during his presidency. This process preceded the extradition, but the Public Prosecutor's Office appealed and thus brought the case back into play.
Trinity helps 6,000 young people at risk
The organization was created to help children without education not to be on the fringes of society.
The balance of the first 25 years of existence of the organization of social support of Trinj is very important: 6,000 young people who were threatened with social exclusion have been helped. The organization for 25 years helps them to overcome difficult situations.
To this must be added the long hundred jobs that have been acquired for this social group.
Yesterday’s anniversary also served to introduce the balance sheet as part of a ceremonial act that took place in the former production facilities of Fabra i Coats and attended by more than 300 people.
The Trinity Organization was founded in the Trinitat Vella district in 1986 to help young people with low education, without work, struggling with drug addiction or in a situation where they could fall into social exclusion.
Yesterday’s meeting in Sant Andreu was attended by a large number of representatives of organizations and institutions that have worked with the association for the past 25 years.
The diverse political representation, during the elections, showed the unified nature of the work carried out by the Trinity.
Together with the President of the Generalitat, Artur Mas, and his predecessor, Jordi Pujol, the ceremonial act was attended by former socialist education adviser, Ernest Maragall, and former deputy mayor and current eco-socialist councillor, Ricard Goma.
