There was an eviction of the house taken away, in which gigantic parties were held
Intruders seized 11 of 13 apartments in Balmes, 51
12 occupiers left the house yesterday at noon without resisting
Everything suggests that the nightmare experienced by the neighbors of 51 Balmes Street is finally over.
Twelve people voluntarily left the building they were illegally inhabiting yesterday at noon, where they organized gigantic parties to wake up the neighbors. They left the building by court order without the need for police intervention.
At the end of the operation, the lock on the door was replaced to prevent a recurrence of the situation.
"From now on, the entrance will be guarded," the administrator said.
The occupants, who took 11 of the 13 apartments in the building - the rest are inhabited - took away all the electrical and partly water equipment, in addition to painting the walls and leaving behind all kinds of garbage, especially cans of alcoholic beverages.
In the first three apartments, huge parties took place, lasting up to two days, and woke up the other tenants.
Next to the building is a disco, Balmes 51, which was also damaged.
Its owner, Maria Pantinat, explained to Europa Press that while the building was occupied, sales fell by 80%.
The owner of the discotheque stresses that the occupants of the building made her unfair competition because they sold drinks for 3 euros, while the discotheque costs 10 euros.
In addition, the owner of the entertainment business had to respond to the complaints of the neighbors about the noise. But the problems were not caused by the visitors of the discotheque, but the inhabitants of the house taken, and especially those who participated in the parties organized here, whose frequency and intensity has increased in recent weeks, according to the eyes of the
The owner of the disco explained that the problems were so great that they even agreed with the owner of the building and forgave her for nine months.
The city police also confirmed that in recent weeks they have received more complaints from neighbors about the situation.
The head of the city group of the PP People's Party at the town hall, Alberto Fernández Díaz, last week called for "the building to be moved immediately and thus end the problems of civic coexistence suffered by the neighbors and the destruction of the area".
The Prime Minister explained that only one floor had been removed before the summer, but in recent months the occupiers had entered all the floors of the building and almost all the apartments, and in one of them there were even thefts.
In this regard, he added that "it is necessary to end impunity and be consistent when it comes to the acts against civil responsibility that took place in the building".
Yesterday, the city police also cleared the building in Nou Barris.
At 3:30 p.m., police entered the 35th building on Mont-ral Street after being summoned by neighbors who saw four people entering the building.
All four were immediately detained.
