The architects met on the occasion of writing out the procedure, which carries with it more than a controversy about fees
The city’s 16-gate competition reopens the debate on the role of Collserola Park in Barcelona.
In the mid-1980s, at the time of the greatest bloom, the already extinct Corporación Metropolitana de Barcelona (CMB), this municipality printed several pamphlets in support of the Collserola Park.
The leaflet defined the mountain as a large metropolitan park in Barcelona.
What's more, it was supplemented by a numerical comparison with New York's Central Park.
After the disappearance of the CMB in 1987, the park returned to the minds of many as the top of Barcelona. The Catalan metropolis is one of the few that does not focus on the north-south axis, but up (mountain) - down (sea).
The qualification of Collserola as a natural park goes in this direction.
The reference was no longer Central Park, but Yellowstone with wildlings instead of the Yogi bear.
That was the position until September, when the town hall declared a mega contest consisting of 16 contests for the same number of entrance gates to Collserola.
Of course, the gate captures the idea of the park.
Either this or someone's trying to place the gate on the field.
So the only question is: Collserola, park or mountain?
During the competition, both from a purely organizational point of view and on the basis of reflection on the city, this issue becomes the central theme of all Barcelona architects.
It is already a topic as blunt as when two members of this old caste, chosen during a meeting in the elevator, shake hands.
And it was this act that sparked one of the rare coincidences between what three Barcelona architects and prominent university professors think.
Miguel Roldán, Daniel Modol and Marta Bayona: the competition has its justification.
According to Roldán, after the question of the Gulf side began, "it is necessary" to discuss the "mountain side" as well, so Ildefonso Cerdo's speech on green apples was not touched upon until the end.
“We have to assume that Barcelona’s largest park is the beach.
Among other things, its high availability.
Collserola is more complex," said the architect, for whom the name "the gate to Collserola" carries a "lexicological trap": we must not imagine them "as entrances to the park, but rather as defining areas where it is possible to operate".
Modol, like Roldán and Bayona, with experience in the world of urbanism, qualifies the proposal as an "intellectual challenge" posing "some dangers".
The danger of "the uncertainty that the public place project presents today" after the experience of the 1980s, which had its "swan singing" in the Forum area.
The first concern is the very definition of the boundaries where it should be built.
"Defining something means taking the next step," that is, basically taking it one step further.
"It is necessary to keep in mind the new urban planning and planning tools, because the current ones (with reference to the General Metropolitan Plan (PGM)) can cause a real disaster."
If we look in more detail at the question, Modol believes that the Collserola valley slope can be "considered a park", but the Barcelona part does not, for purely topographical reasons.
Modol also recalled that there is already work done by the Patronat de Collserola, which "must not end up in the garbage dump", although he welcomes the fact that the town hall offers his body that will intervene in the project from the "first moment".
In addition, he understands that the proximity of the mountain and the city is some sort of leak that allows architects to engage in the debate, but "does doubt" that it should be this technical profile that will lead multidisciplinary teams ("it's all about skills", he adds), which need to be created: "Architects should be able to
Bayona suggests that the answer to the question that gave the name to this game is complex, because there is a lack of Collserola's global vision in the tender documents: "There have been 16 tenders that deal with all the axis of the mountain - the sea, but there is no such longitudinal study that would take place on the whole".
This means that at least he has signed up for all 16 nominations.
Otherwise, the design of a single gate may interfere with the concept and definition of an architect of a neighboring gate.
In his opinion, the town hall should ensure that the zone located directly above the Ronda de Dalt should provide a full-length zone of equipment to ensure a smooth transition between the city and the greenery.
The casino pardoned Jonas Larrazábal, who will be released
After 72 days of imprisonment, legal representative Cadino Red pardoned his brother, Mayor of Monterrey, in a trial in which he was prosecuted for alleged blackmail.
Manuel Jonas Larrazábal spent 72 days in prison and will now be released after Casino Red’s legal representative granted him a pardon before the Second Criminal Court in that district, which was investigating a case of blackmail in which Mayor Monterrey’s brother was charged.
After the assassination of Casino Royale, Casino Red owner Sergio Gil García published a series of photos and videos in which Manuel Jonas was to ask him to pay the economic quota to allow the Monterrey City Hall to operate illegally at the betting house.
After public prosecution, the State Prosecutor's Office began prosecuting the brother of the Panist mayor. On 2 September, he was arrested and imprisoned for 30 days.
Then, after 4 hours spent in front of the Public Prosecutor’s Office, No. 3 for property crimes was transferred to Prison 1, located in the Barrio Antiguo in the state’s capital.
He remained at the scene for the next 49 days after the second detention decree was issued and a Public Prosecutor’s Office agent denied the possibility of involvement or organized crime.
On October 19, he was transferred to the Cadereyta Criminal Court on suspicion of blackmailing the owners of Casino Red in the amount of one and a half million pesos. However, he remained in prison for only a few hours with moderate surveillance because he was threatened with death.
During the trial, he was allowed to remain in city cells in San Nicolás de los Garza.
On 25 October, he was presented with an arrest warrant issued by the secretary of the Second Criminal Court, Jorge Yanez, who stated that after almost two months of investigation, enough evidence had been collected to prove Jonas' guilt. Among the evidence will be that a million pesos will be paid for, for example, part of a cassette.
This Monday, Casina Red's legal representative, Víctor Aldo García Gómez, handed over to Judge José Luis Pecin and asked for mercy for the brother of the mayor of the region. On the basis of this, he will be able to return to freedom soon.
During the legal hearing, the Attorney General's representative to the court, Ramiro Arias, asked García Gómez if the damage had been repaired and who of the associates decided to grant pardon, but the lawyer made it clear that the name would remain secret.
On the basis of the official file 197/2011, Jonas Larrazábal is granted legal pardon. In the process that was conducted against him, it will not be possible to file any complaint. It is also not possible to request compensation for damages or punishment.
After a hearing with the legal representative at around 15:50, the court ordered the immediate release of Larrazábal Bretón.
The clerk of the court, Jorge Yanez, came to the prison in the town of San Nicolás de los Garza to inform Jonas that he had been granted an official pardon and his case had been deposited in the archives.
He also informed him that the judge had issued an immediate order for his release.
Secretary Dionisio Pérez Jácome gave details of the plane crash that killed the governor's secretary, Francisco Blake, and seven others.
The Secretariat for Communications and Transport (SCT) reported that the results of an investigation into the accident that killed Secretary of State Francisco Blake Mora and seven others indicate that the helicopter hit the ground in full force without the pilot having a chance to attempt a forced landing.
At a press conference, Dionisio Pérez Jácome, secretary for Communications and Transport, said that before the aircraft took off, the pilot noted that the climatic conditions allow for flights.
"Parts that appear indicate that the unit came into contact with the terrain several times, the wings were entangled in branches of trees 25 meters from where the unit lost its hull."
He also informed that the unit was intended for 19 people, therefore it met all requirements for the transport of personnel.
In addition, it stated that no components were found on the ground on the basis of an investigation carried out in the area of impact.
"During the search, it was found that parts of the aircraft are not located elsewhere, so the aircraft collided with the ground as a whole.
"The helicopter was designed for 19 people, met all requirements for the transportation of people.
The terrain shows a slope with a slope of seven to thirty degrees.
The secretary assured that at the moment it is most important to get results as quickly as possible. However, the investigation can take several months or up to one year.
Gilberto López Meyer, Director General of Airports and Auxiliary Services, said that at the moment of the collision, the helicopter of the Presidential General Staff was moving at excursion speed and the accident occurred on a soft ascent terrain.
"This information supports the hypothesis that at the time of the accident it was a normal overflight operation," he said.
At the press conference, SCT representative Pérez Jácome listed six main points of the investigation:
Visual flight:
In accordance with aviation standards, the flight was carried out according to the rules of visual flight, that is, the crew must see on the ground during the flight.
Meteorological conditions:
Reports in the AICM indicate adequate conditions at takeoff, according to which the aircraft proceeds towards the border, between the DF and the State of Mexico there were visible layers of clouds at low altitudes.
Selected routes:
It is likely that because of the clouds, the crew was looking for a lower area and greater visibility to the Cuernavaca Valley.
Location of the impact.
The collision coordinates and the last recording of the helicopter from the radar coincide, it is likely that there was no loss of control or disruption of the flight trajectory before the impact.
Dissipation of aircraft remnants in restricted territory:
The information we currently have allows us to assume that the collision occurred on a straight trajectory and from the side.
The plane's scattering pattern indicates that the helicopter was intact at the time of the landing.
There was no fire or explosion.
There was no evidence at the scene of the accident that there was an explosion or a fire.
The latest results of the investigation indicate that there may have been several contacts with the land.
During fieldwork, the remains of the aircraft were found at an altitude of up to 9,200 feet above sea level, the terrain is weighed, the height of the slope goes from seven to 30 degrees.
The photographs show shots in which there was probably a breakdown along the aforementioned route.
The information provides elements that appear to indicate that the helicopter could have come into contact with the ground in several places.
After careful search around the accident, in a territory that is larger than the landing area, the remains of the helicopter were not found, which reinforces the assumption that the collision occurred in a state when the helicopter was still intact.
Mexican Institute of Health Insurance Launches Research on the Gene that Causes Obesity
The Institute of Health Insurance conducts research in order to discover the gene responsible for obesity in children and adolescents. The research is carried out with the support of experts from the IPN Institute
The Mexican Institute of Health Insurance (IMSS) has announced that it is conducting research aimed at detecting the gene that causes obesity in children and adolescents. Research called "Genetics of obesity in children and adolescents" will allow to obtain results related to overweight.
In a report, Miguel Cruz López, head of the Research Medical Unit in Biochemistry at the Specialized Hospital of the National Health Center of the 21st Century, explained that a multidisciplinary team of doctors, nurses, nutritionists and social workers had been set up.
This team is supported by specialists and postgraduate students from the National Institute of Public Health (INSP) and the Center for Research and Advanced Studies (Cinvesta) of the National Polytechnic Institute (IPN).
The general public, whether authorized or not, can also participate in the research. People can come to the participating sports centers of IMSS in Valle de México, where they will be tested by juveniles every council from 8 a.m.
He stressed that the research began at the Cuauhtémoc Sports Center (Mexico State) and since 8 October this activity is also carried out at the Nezahualcóyolt Sports Center (East of the Mexican State).
Once data from 500 to 600 children have been obtained, the study will continue at the Independencia Sports Center (south of the Federal District) and eventually at the Morelos Sports Center (north of the Federal Center).
He explained that the purpose of this research is to determine the components and significance of genetics in terms of the development of obesity, and to track down risk factors in Mexican children and young people, thereby preventing the development of chronic degenerative diseases.
On the occasion of International Diabetes Day, which is celebrated on November 14, he recalled that the goal is to collect data from 3,000 children and young people between the ages of six and 14, with the consent and under the supervision of parents, for the application of specific questionnaires on nutrition.
The questionnaire will also ask about physical activity and family history of hereditary diseases in order to avoid risk factors that could cause diseases such as diabetes or kidney failure.
He clarified that anthropometric measurements (weight, height, waist circumference) are performed every Saturday with all participants, blood pressure is measured, glucose, triglycerides, cholesterol, insulin levels are determined, and genes are examined (trying to identify the genes that are involved in the development).
Cruz López said the research reflects health professionals’ concerns about the alarming increase in child weight.
'Health surveys conducted between 1999 and 2006 showed that in just six years, there was only a 77% increase in obesity in boys and 47% in girls. There was also a dramatic increase in overweight', said the expert from IMSS.
He said that one of the reasons for looking for indicators is the assumption that the population of the country differs from other populations by its genetic history.
